## Regression on ggplot


::: {.cell output-location='column' fig.asp='0.7'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = nlsy, 
       aes(x = age_bir, y = income)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](tables_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-26-1.png){width=576}
:::
:::


This corresponds to 

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
lm(income ~ age_bir, data = nlsy)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```

Call:
lm(formula = income ~ age_bir, data = nlsy)

Coefficients:
(Intercept)      age_bir  
     1706.6        594.9  
```
:::
:::


## Stratified regression


::: {.cell fig.asp='0.7' output-location='column'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = nlsy, 
       aes(x = age_bir, y = income)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") +
  facet_grid(cols = vars(sex_cat),
             rows = vars(race_eth_cat))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](tables_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-28-1.png){width=576}
:::
:::


This corresponds to 

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
linear_model <- lm(income ~ sex_cat*age_bir*race_eth_cat, 
                   data = nlsy)
```
:::


## Other models


::: {.cell fig.asp='0.7' output-location='column'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = nlsy, 
       aes(x = age_bir, 
           y = income)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(formula = y ~ x +
                I(x^2) + I(x^3),
              method = "lm")
```

